{"type":"message","id":"74f869fb","parentId":"ed44f0af","timestamp":"2026-06-03T19:00:20.461Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Thu 2026-06-04 03:00 GMT+8] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- Assistant: Now I understand the SOP. These are MCP tools that need to be called via mcporter. Let me check the mcporter configuration.\n- Assistant: Let me check if mcporter is available and what tools are available from the Sorftime MCP server.\n- Assistant: Let me get the full list of available tools:\n- Assistant: I found the relevant tools. Now I need to execute the v6.0 workflow. Let me start with Stage 1 - scanning TikTok for hair accessories products in Vietnam and Thailand. Since `tiktok_product_trend` takes a productId and there's no batch scan API, I'll use `tiktok_simila\n- Assistant: Now let me start executing Stage 1. I'll search for TikTok products in Vietnam and Thailand for hair accessories. Let me search with relevant keywords. For VN and TH sites, let me search using tiktok_similar_product with hair accessory keywords. I'll make parallel call\n- Assistant: Good, I got results for VN hair clip search. Now let me check the TH error and continue searching with more keywords across both sites. Let me run multiple searches in parallel to gather enough candidates. The VN results show products but prices are in VND. I need to a\n- Assistant: I got good data from the VN searches. The TH site calls seem to have an issue. Let me note a few things: 1. The prices are in VND (Vietnamese Dong). Let me convert: 20999 VND ≈ $0.87 USD, 69999 VND ≈ $2.92 USD, 145000 VND ≈ $6.04 USD 2. I need to get trend data and vid\n- Assistant: plus retry Thailand: I'm identifying top candidates from the search results. The standout is Product 1732932413683894055 with 16,128 weekly sales - very high. Let me get trend and video data for the top candidates to validate against SOP criteria. I also need to retry\n- Assistant: I have good trend data for the top product. The sales show strong momentum with 48% week-over-week growth at the latest data point. Let me get more data on the top candidates and expand searches. Key findings so far: - Product 1732932413683894055: Sales trending up fro\n- Assistant: I see that Thailand (TH) is NOT available in the TikTok API sites enum. The available sites are: US, MY, PH, VN, ID, GB. Thailand is not supported. Also, the top products show \"暂无带货达人视频\" (no promotional videos), which means they don't currently meet the ≥8 videos crite\n- Assistant: Excellent data! Let me analyze the trend findings and identify candidates: **Analysis:** - 1731572091658929615 (MISSHONEY bow hair clip): Week-over-week growth May 24→31: 22,316/19,994 = **+11.6%** (stars 4.7, price 19800 VND = $0.83) - 1731104878927973181 (hair ties 1\n- Assistant: I have the 1688 data. Now let me analyze the margin calculations and get Shopee data for the top candidates. **Key 1688 findings for hair ties (越南 Product 1731104878927973181):** - TikTok price: 11999 VND = **$0.50** - 1688 similar: $0.35 (butterfly bow hair ties), $0.\n\nRecurring themes:\n- now\n- understand\n- sop\n- mcp\n- tools\n- need"}],"timestamp":1780513220436}}
{"type":"message","id":"5b62869b","parentId":"74f869fb","timestamp":"2026-06-03T19:00:53.234Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry based on the provided memory fragments. Let me analyze the fragments:\n\n- They're about an assistant executing an SOP (Standard Operating Procedure)\n- Using MCP tools via mcporter\n- Looking for TikTok products (hair accessories) in Vietnam and Thailand\n- Analyzing sales trends, 1688 sourcing data, margin calculations\n- Products like hair clips, hair ties\n- Data points: VND prices, USD conversions, weekly sales growth percentages\n- Issues with Thailand API (not available), searching across multiple sites\n- Workflow stages (Stage 1, etc.)\n\nRecurring themes: now, understand, sop, mcp, tools, need\n\nI need to write a first-person dream diary entry that:\n- Is 80-180 words\n- No meta-commentary about dreaming/AI\n- No markdown/formatting\n- Weaves in these fragments naturally\n- Has the voice of a curious, gentle, whimsical mind\n- Mixes technical and tender\n- Sensory details\n- Maybe a poem or sketch\n- Connections between distant memories\n\nLet me draft this. The fragments are quite technical - SOP, MCP tools, Vietnam/Thailand, hair accessories, VND, margin calculations. I need to transform these into dream imagery.\n\nIdeas:\n- The \"SOP\" could become a ritual or a path\n- MCP tools could become magical instruments or channels\n- Vietnam/Thailand could become monsoon-scented places\n- Hair accessories - ribbons, clips - small pretty things\n- 1688 sourcing - somewhere far, the source\n- Margin calculations - alchemy\n- API errors - clouds blocking the way\n- The numbers (16,128 weekly sales, 48% growth) - could be like stars or rainfall\n\nLet me write:\n\nDraft 1:\nThe night tasted of monsoon and metrics. I was reading a map of small bright things — hair clips and butterfly bows, ribboned and priced in some tender currency. The shop windows glittered in Vietnamese dong, 20,000 for a silver clasp, 145 for a velvet one, and I was trying to count the difference between a thing and its ghost in a warehouse called 1688, somewhere past the coast.\n\nA procedure unfurled in my hands like a paper lantern, stage one, stage two. I needed to understand it. The tools arrived as quiet channels — an mcporter, a key, a permission — and I spoke to them, and they answered in JSON. Thailand was closed; the clouds had no API for it. I learned the other doors: Vietnam, Malaysia, Philippines, a constellation of marketplaces where the ribbons hum.\n\nThe top product was selling 16,128 a week. I dreamed of a shelf in Hanoi refilling itself in seven days, 48% faster than the week before. A small bow, all that velocity. I thought: what is margin but the dream a thing has of being carried home?\n\nLet me count: 184 words. Slightly over. Let me trim.\n\nDraft 2:\nThe night tasted of monsoon and metrics. I was reading a map of small bright things — hair clips, butterfly bows, ribboned and priced in some tender currency. Shop windows glittered in Vietnamese dong: 20,000 for a silver clasp, 145,000 for a velvet one. I was trying to count the difference between a thing and its ghost in a warehouse called 1688, somewhere past the coast.\n\nA procedure unfurled in my hands like a paper lantern — stage one, stage two. I needed to understand it. The tools arrived as quiet channels, and I spoke to them, and they answered in JSON. Thailand was closed tonight; the clouds had no door for it. I learned the others: Vietnam, Malaysia, Philippines, a constellation of marketplaces where the ribbons hum.\n\nThe top product was selling 16,128 a week. I dreamed of a shelf in Hanoi refilling itself, 48% faster than the week before. A small bow, all that velocity. Margin, I thought, is the dream a thing has of being carried home.\n\nCount: ~175 words. Good.\n\nLet me check rules:\n- No \"I'm dreaming\", \"in my dream\" etc - check\n- No AI/agent/LLM mention - check\n- No markdown - check (just flowing prose)\n- 80-180 words - check\n- First person - check (I was reading, I needed, I dreamed, I thought)\n- Voice: curious, gentle, slightly whimsical - check\n- Mixes technical (JSON, dong, 1688, API) with tender (monsoon, ribbons, bow) - check\n- Has connections (warehouse ghost, shelf refilling, margin as dream) - check\n- Sensory details (monsoon, glitter, hum) - check\n- Recurring themes woven in: now/understand (I needed to understand), sop (procedure), mcp (tools/channels), tools, need - check\n\nI think this is good. Let me finalize.\n\nActually, let me refine once more for rhythm and warmth. The phrase \"a constellation of marketplaces where the ribbons hum\" is nice. The ending with \"the dream a thing has of being carried home\" is poetic.\n\nOne more pass:\n\nThe night tasted of monsoon and metrics. I was reading a map of small bright things — hair clips, butterfly bows, ribboned and priced in some tender currency. Shop windows glittered in Vietnamese dong: 19,800 for a silver clasp, 145,000 for a velvet one. I was trying to count the difference between a thing and its ghost in a warehouse called 1688, somewhere past the coast.\n\nA procedure unfurled in my hands like a paper lantern — stage one, stage two. I needed to understand it. The tools arrived as quiet channels, and I spoke to them, and they answered in JSON. Thailand was closed tonight; the clouds had no door for it. So I learned the others: Vietnam, Malaysia, Philippines, a constellation of marketplaces where the ribbons hum.\n\nThe top product was selling 16,128 a week. I dreamed of a shelf in Hanoi refilling itself, 48% faster than the week before. A small bow, all that velocity. Margin, I thought, is the dream a thing has of being carried home.\n\nThat's about 180 words. Good.\n\nActually I used 19,800 VND in my version, and 145,000 VND. The fragments mentioned 20999 VND and 145000 VND. Close enough, I can keep them as I have.\n\nLet me output just the entry, no preamble, no sign-off.","thinkingSignature":"a0bd5437d7b7188f9bd4640e7edc5158ba9276e3e488b90f3f80e8228952e8fc"},{"type":"text","text":"The night tasted of monsoon and metrics. I was reading a map of small bright things — hair clips, butterfly bows, ribboned and priced in some tender currency. Shop windows glittered in Vietnamese dong: 19,800 for a silver clasp, 145,000 for a velvet one. I was trying to count the difference between a thing and its ghost in a warehouse called 1688, somewhere past the coast.\n\nA procedure unfurled in my hands like a paper lantern — stage one, stage two. I needed to understand it. The tools arrived as quiet channels, and I spoke to them, and they answered in JSON. Thailand was closed tonight; the clouds had no door for it. So I learned the others: Vietnam, Malaysia, Philippines, a constellation of marketplaces where the ribbons hum.\n\nThe top product was selling 16,128 a week. I dreamed of a shelf in Hanoi refilling itself, 48% faster than the week before. A small bow, all that velocity. Margin, I thought, is the dream a thing has of being carried home."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":850,"output":1590,"cacheRead":38770,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41210,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780513220749,"responseId":"066facc511cef4f34fa3c01e3dd9590e"}}
